issue.title: Complete the BIP155 implementation and upgrade to TORv3
issue.body:
This PR contains the two remaining commits from #19031 to complete the [BIP155](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0155.mediawiki) implementation:

`net: CAddress & CAddrMan: (un)serialize as ADDRv2`
`net: advertise support for ADDRv2 via new message`

plus one more commit:

`tor: make a TORv3 hidden service instead of TORv2`

issue.title: Implement ADDRv2 support (part of BIP155)
issue.body:
An implementation of [BIP155](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0155.mediawiki) `addrv2` messages. To ease review it is split in a few logical changes and submitted as separate, smaller, PRs.

The current one for review is: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19954

Preparation changes
---
Commits:
* [x] `test: add an edge case test for CSubNet` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19351)
* [x] `net: improve encapsulation of CNetAddr` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19360)
* [x] `net: document enum Network` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19534)
* [x] `net: save the network type explicitly in CNetAddr` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19534)

Change `CNetAddr::ip` to have flexible size
---
Commits:
* [x] `net: change CNetAddr::ip to have flexible size` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19628)

Implement `addrv2` (un)serializing
---
Add support to serialize `CNetAddr` and `CAddress` in [ADDRv2](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0155.mediawiki#specification) format. Invoke that from `CAddrMan` serialization methods. Commits:
* [x] `net: move HasPrefix() so it can be reused` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19845)
* [x] `test: move HasReason() so it can be reused` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19845)
* [x] `net: CNetAddr: add support to (un)serialize as ADDRv2` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19845)
* [x] `net: recognize TORv3/I2P/CJDNS networks` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19845)
* [x] `net: CAddress & CAddrMan: (un)serialize as ADDRv2` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19954)

Advertise support
---
Advertise `ADDRv2` support to peers, handle incoming `ADDRv2` messages and send to peers in that format if they have advertised support. Commits:
* [x] `net: advertise support for ADDRv2 via new message` (merged via https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19954)

All the steps to get Tor v3 support are outlined in [issue#18884 Tor v3 support](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/18884), this PR is one of them.
